# Cursor & AI Rules Sync

`vibeCodingRules` is the **canonical store** for universal AI-session rules. Projects use `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` copies.

---

## Source of Truth

| Location | Role |
|----------|------|
| `vibeCodingRules/*.md` | Human-readable rules; listed in `AGENTS.md` |
| `vibeCodingRules/AGENTS.md` | Routing authority for all rule files |
| `vibeCodingRules/cursor/*.mdc` | Cursor drop-in (frontmatter + body or AGENTS pointer) |
| `<project>/.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Per-project install |

Body text in paired `.md` and `.mdc` files MUST stay aligned (`.mdc` adds YAML frontmatter only). `cursor/vibe-rulebook.mdc` is the exception: it is a pointer to `AGENTS.md`, not a duplicate source.

---

## When to Update

Update `vibeCodingRules` whenever you:

- Add, change, or remove a Cursor rule in any project
- Change token-efficiency or discovery/grill policy
- Add a new always-on AI behavior rule

**Order:** edit `vibeCodingRules` first -> copy `cursor/*.mdc` to project `.cursor/rules/`.

---

## Adding a New Rule

1. Create `vibeCodingRules/<name>.md` with sections (The Rule, DO, DON'T).
2. Create `vibeCodingRules/cursor/<name>.mdc` with `description`, `alwaysApply` or `globs`.
3. Update `AGENTS.md` - Rule Catalog tables, task routing row, and per-edit checklist if behavior is universal.
4. Copy `.mdc` into active projects.

## Full rulebook mirror (Cursor)

**Minimum install** (every project): `vibe-rulebook.mdc`, `token-efficiency.mdc`, `feature-discovery.mdc`, `naming.mdc`, `documentation.mdc`, plus per-project sync rule.

**Full mirror:** For each universal behavior agents must follow without opening the repo, maintain a paired `cursor/<topic>.mdc` whose body matches the root `*.md` (YAML frontmatter only). `vibe-rulebook.mdc` stays a pointer to `AGENTS.md` - not a duplicate of all chapters.

When grilling updates policy, edit root `*.md` first, then update the paired `.mdc`, then copy to projects.

---

## Repo Path

`[DEFAULT]` canonical clone path is machine-specific (e.g. `~/Github/vibeCodingRules`). Override per machine; keep the relative layout (`cursor/`, root `*.md`) the same.
